The paper deals with image super-resolution, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of Bayesian methods and Markov random fields suggests that the paper may also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of variational Bayesian methods and optimization techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
